From : {bold}Paul Mattson{nobold} <->
{p} {p}
Greetings all,
{p} {p}
I have aquired an Amiga 2000 with the Video Toaster to manipulate the
cameras and lyrics display in our church.{p}
For ease of use, I want to replace the mouse with a trackball. I have tried
a PC serial trackball, but it does not work.{p}
Someone told me that it needs to be rewired to work on the Amiga, but nobody
seems to know which pins need to go where.{p}
I have searched the internet; but am unable to find a schematic for the
Amiga mouse, or which pins to swap on a standard PC serial mouse to make it
work.
{p} {p}
I hope someone here has this information and can fill me in.
{p} {p}
May God bless the one that helps his servant.
{p} {p}
Thank you,{p}
Paul Mattson {p}
Ptochos@USFamily.net{p}
{p} {p}
{italic}Editor's reply:  Software Hut carries the Topolino which I know
to work quite well with my own Logitek trackball.  There is also a new
product called MROOCHECK which supports wheel mice.{noitalic}
